UPDATE users_data SET heart_rate = ? , blood_pressure = ? , temperature = ?, glucose = ?, oxygen = ?, INR = ?, weight = ? , height = ? , BMI = ? , period_start = ? , period_end = ?, feeding_type = ?, last_fed = ?, gestation_period = ?, birth_order = ? WHERE user_id = ?

INSERT INTO `users` (`email`,`password`,`token`,`token_date`,`registration_date`) VALUES (#[flowVars.email],#[flowVars.password_encrypted],#[flowVars.token],#[server.dateTime.format("yyyy.MM.dd' 'HH:mm:ss")],#[server.dateTime.format("yyyy.MM.dd' 'HH:mm:ss")]);
http://www.mulesoft.org/schema/mule/db/select
select * from `users_info` where `user_id` = #[payload.'user_id'] limit 1;
select authentication.auth_token, users.password, users.status from `users` inner join `authentication` on users.user_id = authentication.user_id where users.email = #[payload.'email'] limit 1;
SELECT users_data. * , users_info.gender , users_info.birthday FROM users_data INNER JOIN users_info WHERE users_data.user_id = #[payload.user_id] AND users_info.user_id = #[payload.user_id]
select relation.member_id , users_info.f_name from relation inner join users_info on relation.user_id = #[payload.'user_id'] and relation.member_id = users_info.user_id and relation.status = 1;
SELECT token_date FROM users WHERE email = #[message.payload.email] AND token = #[message.payload.token]
SELECT users_data. * , users_info.gender , users_info.birthday FROM users_data INNER JOIN users_info WHERE users_data.user_id = #[payload.user_id] AND users_info.user_id = #[payload.user_id]
http://www.mulesoft.org/schema/mule/db/update
UPDATE users SET password = #[payload] , token = "expired" , `status` = 1 WHERE email = #[message.payload.email]
UPDATE users SET password = #[payload] , token = "expired" , `status` = 1 WHERE email = ?

UPDATE relation SET confirmation_chk = 1 WHERE user_id = (SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE email= #[message.payload.user_email] ) AND member_id = (SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE email= #[message.payload.member_email] ) AND confirmation_chk = 0 AND confirmation_token = #[message.payload.token]
UPDATE relation SET `status` = 1 WHERE user_id = #[message.payload.user_id] AND member_id = #[message.payload.member_id] AND status = 0 AND token = #[message.payload.token]

UPDATE relation SET `status` = 1 WHERE user_id = (SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE email= #[message.payload.user_email] ) AND member_id = (SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE email= #[message.payload.member_email] ) AND status = 0 AND token = #[message.payload.token]
UPDATE `users` SET token = #[payload], token_date = ? WHERE email = ?
